quran[10]{c,v,t,f}:
  96,19,"No! Do not obey him. But prostrate and draw near [to Allāh]."
  100,7,"And indeed, he is to that a witness.{1}",1:[Through his speech and his actions.]
  100,8,"And indeed he is, in love of wealth, intense."
  100,9,"But does he not know that when the contents of the graves are scattered"
  101,4,"It is the Day when people will be like moths, dispersed,{1}",1:[The people will be as such after having been expelled from their graves.]
  101,5,"And the mountains will be like wool, fluffed up.{1}",1:[i.e., beginning to disintegrate.]
  101,6,"Then as for one whose scales are heavy [with good deeds],"
  102,1,"Competition in [worldly] increase diverts you"
  102,2,"Until you visit the graveyards.{1}",1:[i.e., remain in them temporarily, meaning until the Day of Resurrection.]
  102,3,"No! You are going to know."